<TITLE> Changes in administration </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 7 (bdnews24.com) -- The government on Sunday made some changes in the administration. The establishment ministry issued separate notifications in this regard. Additional secretary working as the housing project director at Prime Minister's Office (PMO) Liaquat Ali was transferred to the Board of Investment as its director. Establishment ministry officer on special duty (OSD) joint secretary Matiar Rahman was posted to Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Authority (BIWTA) as a member. He replaced Abdul Monnaf Patwary, who was seconded to Bangladesh Forest Industries Development Corporation as a director. BCS Administration Academy director Quazi Rowshan Akter, Power Development Board secretary Azizul Islam and National Sports Council director Subrata Roy Mitra were made directors at PMO with the status of deputy secretary. OSD deputy secretary Shah Mohammad Nasim was posted as the director of a project to accomplish works of BIAM Foundation headquarters. Finance division deputy secretary Hawlader Zakir Hossain was made Mongla Port Authority director to replace Taposh Kumar Basu, who was transferred to the Directorate of Land Records and Survey as its deputy director. Deputy secretary working as Anti-Corruption Commission deputy director Selim Reza was transferred to Bangladesh Public Administration Training Centre as its director. 
